				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1232784/scp-2602-which-used-to-be-a-library#post-3680415</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 13 Jan 2018 01:45:05 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>1577196</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm kinda sad that the author said that the effect isn't consistent all the way back on page 1, because you <em>can</em> read it consistently.</p> <p>The (hazard-affected) article text says that actuarial tables can be used to measure the expected damage to SCP-2602, which used to be a library. It also said that &quot;Dewey radiation&quot; is emitted by &quot;damaged library patrons,&quot; and that restraints used &quot;to hold patrons with overdue books&quot; were damaged by &quot;book-sorting machines.&quot;</p> <p>What if this facility was processing &quot;patrons&quot; into &quot;books?&quot;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
