					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1232784#post-2928445</guid>
				<title>Re: Huh?</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1232784/scp-2602-which-used-to-be-a-library#post-2928445</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 27 Jun 2017 04:56:02 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Relevart</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3126342</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>&quot;Exbibliothetic&quot; is the title on the Series 3 page, but &quot;SCP-2602, which used to be a library&quot; is the title of the page itself (whereas 99% of SCPs are just &quot;SCP-XXXX&quot;). That's why &quot;SCP-2602, which used to be a library&quot; shows up at the top of the discussion page, in the &quot;Top Rated Pages&quot; listing, and in other places where standard titles don't show up.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1232784#post-2928425</guid>
				<title>Re: Huh?</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1232784/scp-2602-which-used-to-be-a-library#post-2928425</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 27 Jun 2017 04:54:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>sirpudding</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>348648</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>Oh, well I stand corrected then. I am just wondering why I distinctly remembering this being called what I said it was.</p> </blockquote> <p>You could go through the history on Series III and see if it was ever different, but I don't think it was.</p> <blockquote> <p>As for the second part…well, you can tell how much I know about the English language then. I stand corrected.</p> </blockquote> <p>It's Latin.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
