					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1232784#post-2927432</guid>
				<title>Re: Huh?</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1232784/scp-2602-which-used-to-be-a-library#post-2927432</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 27 Jun 2017 03:13:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>sirpudding</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>348648</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>Did someone change the title of this? I could have sworn that the title was originally:</p> </blockquote> <p>According to the Series III history it has been &quot;Exbibiliothetic&quot; since June 8th 2015, the day this article was first posted.</p> <blockquote> <p>Further more; it doesn't make any reference to being a former library, so it doesn't even make sense.</p> </blockquote> <p>Yes, it does. &quot;Ex-&quot; can mean &quot;former&quot;; &quot;bibliothetic&quot; means &quot;having the properties of a library&quot;.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
